Bind Multiple Track Tables by Row

Source: R/track.R
rbind_track.Rd

rbind_track uses data.table::rbindlist to combine track tables by rows, but makes sure that you cannot bind together two tables with different projections, that the projection attribute is inherited by the resulting track table, and that track tables based on different table classes are coerced to the same table class.

rbind_track(...)

Arguments

...

Track tables to combine. Each argument can either be a track table or a list of track tables. The track tables must have the same projection.

Value

A track table.

Author

Simon Garnier, garnier@njit.edu

Examples

data(short_tracks)

rbind_track(short_tracks, short_tracks)
